## OpenAI Codex — format interoperability, not vendored code

`packages/coding-agent/src/edit/apply-patch/` and related callers implement
the `apply_patch` patch-envelope *format* popularized by OpenAI's Codex CLI
(`openai/codex`, Apache-2.0) so Veyyon can read/write patches in that shape.
This repository does not vendor Codex source code for that format: the
parser, renderer, and patch application logic under `packages/coding-agent`
and `packages/hashline` are Veyyon/oh-my-pi's own TypeScript implementation.
Likewise, `packages/ai/src/providers/openai-codex-responses.ts` and
`packages/catalog/src/wire/codex.ts` implement a client for OpenAI's public
Codex/ChatGPT backend wire protocol (endpoints, headers, streaming shape) —
protocol interoperability, not copied implementation. No Apache-2.0 notice
carries forward here because no Codex source is present in this tree.

